Dead Man's Windpipe:
Suck into front 2 row slam
(can KBI, do not KBI Car 1)
P.S. you can walk off the edge

I'll only show people 
with defams because
everyone else is on top
of one of them.

Defams seemed random
Sometimes the first was
1Sup 1DPS, others 2D.

They are invulning this so you
can run out and always make it.

Stay up here.
If you fall down you have 
to run all the way around.

Don't jump if a tank jumps,
you usually die if dps in a 2 stack.

Lightning = Down hit
Red light = Up hit

Get safe from 1st,
then go up or fall down,
then STOP MOVING.

SNAP -> move.
Do this together or 
in your melee/range group
or be smart about it.

2 of the same thing have to be smart 
about it, you have time. (2M/2H/2R/2T)
Remember twister comes right after.
Could also have 1 defam just stand on the party.

Stay up, if 2 people go down you die.
Smile

1T and 1H are marked.
They explode when the
ground circle explodes.
It's a stack >3 rows wide.
If you are up and the stack
is down you don't count as
being in it.
2 people in a stack = dead.
If T/H die it to moves to 
another T/H (no cheese).

Make sure you look if the
exit is RIGHT or LEFT

These will disappear 
before turrets.
Only being UP/Down
blocks turrets.
Pretend the blocks
are not real.

notes_raw:
Graphic design is my passion. 

It's too much to explain everything.
A lot of the spaces for stack/spread are basically the same with obstacles the entire fight.

Invulning the towers I marked should make it so only the tank can be slow and die from failing to escape.

Have fun with the revelation sprint.

The rev strat can 100% be refined but this worked.

-Kroxy Cat*Lamia
